    public interface SymbolicObject
    The root of the symbolic object type hierarchy. Represents any kind of symbolic object: symbolic expressions, symbolic types, symbolic expression collections, etc. All symbolic objects provide reasonable hash code methods that are consistent with equals. The kind determines the Java type of this object as follows:
    SYMBOLIC_EXPRESSION SymbolicExpression
    SEQUENCE SymbolicSequence
    TYPE SymbolicType
    TYPE_SEQUENCE SymbolicTypeSequence
    NUMBER NumberObject
    INT IntObject
    BOOLEAN BooleanObject
    STRING StringObject
